HR Specialist
Manpower Professional
Dubai, UAE
Posted on: 30 Apr 2014
THE ROLE
Expand all
A leading multinational automotive organization is seeking to recruit an experienced HR Specialist to be based in their office in Dubai.
The right candidate must have experience in the automotive industry.
You will perform general HR tasks and will be working closely with the HR Manager.
The job will require the below responsibilities:
- Operating HR principle and system as well as developing organization aligned with business strategy.
- Govern employee relations (recruitment, hiring, transfer, termination etc) and employee development demands.
- Implement and standardize HR regulation and policies.
- Manage HR system
- Manage international assignments inbound/outbound with frequent travel to Saudi Arabia
- Initiate continuous improvement at HR related processes.
- Act as HR partner within the region.
REQUIREMENTS
To be considered for this opportunity you must have the following skills and attributes:
-at least 5 years of experience in Human Resources
-Good understanding of the automotive industry
-Excellent Communication Skills in English and Arabic is mandatory
-Willing to travel frequently to GCC countries
ABOUT THE COMPANY
Manpower is the global leader in contingent and permanent staffing, helping organizations and job seekers succeed by connecting the potential of people with the ambitions of business. Manpower helps find and retain top people in IT, accounting, banking, finance, legal, engineering, sales and marketing.
